						p.ar-text In this example, we're going bananas to explore the way Evolve works. You can follow along below or check out an animated tutorial by using the button controls! 
						br
						p.ar-text Logic Chain and Darwin Matrix are two of the EVOLVE cards available in the ROBONOBO deck. Both Actions and Utilities can offer you EVOLVE triggers during the course of the game. 
						br
						p.ar-text Logic Chain is an Action card avaiable in Robonobo's deck. Played by itself, it allows you to Evolve one of your Feats and then deal 2 damage to a single opponent. Logic Chain offers both an immediate EVOLVE trigger and 2 damage to your opponent. Based on ROBONOBO's feats, that could mean drawing a card or forcing your opponent to discard a card or hitting them in the face for two.
						br
						p.ar-text Darwin Matrix is a Utility card avaiable in Robonobo's deck. At the end of each turn, you may Evolve one of your Feats.Unlike Logic Chain, Darwin Matrix doesn't EVOLVE until the end of your turn. That means you'll have to wait until your next turn to use that Feat. That means you can't use this to EVOLVE immediately. On the other hand, Darwin Matrix stays in play from turn-to-turn and will let you EVOLVE forever if left unchecked. 
