						p.ar-text It's the planet of the Apes! Damn it all to hell! 
						br
						p.ar-text To start, let's say that Robonobo has used all of his Feats during this game and has a copy of Wrist Weapon in play.
						br
						p.ar-text Let's play Logic Chain first. This will deal a bit of damage to your opponent, but more importantly it gives us the ability to EVOLVE one of those face-down Feats. Let's EVOLVE our face-down copy of Jailbreak.
						br
						p.ar-text Jailbreak is a Feat card available in Robonobo's character pack. Activated by itself, it lets you draw a card. After playing Logic Chain, our next step is to activate Jailbreak. After using Jailbreak, it gets turned face-down again. Of course, you could always EVOLVE it so that you can use it next turn! 
						br
						p.ar-text Finally, activating Jailbreak had a nice side-effect. Wrist Weapon is a Utility card available in Robonobo's deck. Played by itself, it sits in play waiting for you to activate one of your Feats. When you do activate one of your Feats, it gains an additional +2 Fight for the rest of that turn. If you activate a Feat while Wrist Weapon is in play, Wrist Weapon will instantly get a boost in its Fight Value. Since Wrist Weapon has 0 Fight by default, using a Feat essentially turns Wrist Weapon on.
